The only way that DC will be broken is if it is dispelled. The only way it can be dispelled is if you're soloing a dispelling mob or the mob you're fighting casts an AoE dispell (a la cobalt drakes in CS, or dragons). Until they fix the &quot;Mob will not aggro on Pets while PC in range&quot; thing, no pet will be turned on for more than a brief moment, and it's very very unlikely to be dispelled.<br>
<br>
Besides, I can probably count the number of places that people go for experience that have dispelling mobs on one hand, maybe two. Routinely, I go for weeks or months at a time without seeing a single mob that dispells.<br>
<br>
DC itself may not be overpowered, but combined with other issues, it can be made extreme, surpassing even the Magician Epic pet in damage output, tanking abilities, and reliabilty. <p><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=52886">Rhasin Firestorm</A><BR>
