<br>
I've always considered myself an honest person. by this I mean, if something benefits me at the expense of someone else, I feel pretty uncomfortable about that.<br>
<br>
With that said, what I'm about to say isnt going to make some people happy. I'm sure most Verant employees, enchanters aren't going to like what I'm about to say, but I'm sure most everyone else won't give a damn. But like I said, I'm honest, and honesty and fairness means more to me than not upsetting people.<br>
<br>
So I might as well say it: mobs are overpowered. I mean, my god, these things are like so broken! They have 10k hp, double for 120, and thats just at level 46! Heck, when I DC it, it gets hasted and starts quadding....and when I dictate something, its hitting for 250 a hit, and can be hasted and quadding!<br>
<br>
Let me paint a picture so you understand. Yesterday in Seb, a group was fighting a mob. But not just any mob. This was a dire-charmed, hasted, quadding, fully buffed mob that the chanter had gated on, leaving it with the group. So anyhow, this mob proceeded to go lawnmower on the group, keeled them all in 10 seconds, and then trained itself to the zone via a stupid monk, where it camped the zoneline for 20 minutes before dying. Id say it got about 50 kills, before someone dispelled and slowed it...that must be like 100k damage, and thats without the chanter to control it.<br>
<br>
It gets worse. I'm sure some of you are thinking &quot;Well its only a level 46 mob! It's not that much powerful later!&quot;. Well listen up, bub, 'cause I'm going to let you in on a little secret. It's a little known fact that at levels higher than 46, mobs scale up in power. So do enchanters. Meaning an enchanter with boltrans can do this to froglok krup knights, and an enchanter with Dictate can create an unstoppable engine of death- a hasted, quadding, Aegoed, MRed, Dmg shielded level 58 mob whose hitting for 250-350 dmg a hit, and is set lose on all the players!<br>
<br>
Why am I saying this? Mostly my concience. When these mobs are killing players 4 times as fast as that idiot chanter with the hasted pet, I feel bad. I feel bad that it can kill nonstop with little risk until a shammy slows it. And how is it able to do this? How come the mob is so strong? Because Dire charm lets the enc make it a god! For a mere 27 aa pts, every 72 minutes a chanter can release an ungodly engine of destruction on the world! Every 5 minutes, a chanter with dictate can release something worse!<br>
<br>
The solution to all this is simple. Nerf mob powers. Then they will suck and the pc will resume their place as the most powerful beings per level.<br>
<br>
<br>
/end<br>
<br>
Basically, what I'm saying is that b/c DCable mobs are so strong, the enchanter becomes ungodly. So really, the solution is to debuff your average mob if anything...or keep on upgrading the mage pets. <p>Dexanth Dragonborne <BR>

