<br>
I'm not going to get into this right now... because I'm already an hour late for a raid... and because we've been through this a half dozen times.<br>
<br>
To the extent that this is about Magician Class Balance, I agree that magicians need some upgrades in the post-60 game.  In particular, I would like to see them get a stronger set of Class AAs, including a 9 AA ability, properly scaled.<br>
<br>
To the extent that this is about how overpowered enchanters are, I'm sure you can dig up my previous comments on the subject.  Let me summarize it by the recommendation I gave to my fellow enchanters on Baelish's enchanter boards:<br>
<br>
Unless you do a lot of solo questing/faction farming, or raiding in DC capable areas where Dire Charm could make the difference between success and failure (Kael, especially), hold off on Dire Charm.  While it can be fun, you'll never recouperate the experience you spent on it (9 AAs is a LOT of soloing), and unless you <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> need</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> it, your experience is MUCH better spent on archetype abilities.<br>
-----<br>
<br>
That is my honest opinion. <p>
